[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":1021},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":996,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2024\u002F03\u002F21\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates\u002F":1005},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20240321\u002F3544397426\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":980,"date":981,"description":982,"extension":983,"lang":984,"meta":985,"navigation":413,"path":986,"readingMinutes":987,"seo":988,"standalone":989,"stem":990,"tags":991,"tldr":993,"updated":981,"url":994,"__hash__":995},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fupdate-project-packages-with-npm-check-updates.md","Update Your Project Packages with npm-check-updates","5443974261",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":973},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,32,54,57,96,103,106,121,139,142,149,152,162,168,174,211,223,229,241,244,250,253,267,274,278,287,293,448,459,483,492,875,881,922,925,939,944,947,951,960,969],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Honestly, updating packages on an old project is a massive pain. So here's how to update versions in package.json.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"updating-npm-packages","Updating npm packages",[17,25,26,27,31],{},"Every now and then we update the packages in a project — for new features, bug fixes, or because we need to upgrade Node.js. For me, Node.js upgrades come up often. When you run ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"npm install [package name]",", it installs the version matching your current Node.js. So when you bump Node.js, the package versions follow. At that point you need to update versions in package.json.",[33,34,35],"blockquote",{},[17,36,37,41,42,49,50,53],{},[38,39,40],"strong",{},"Note","\nI'll use a project I built before — \"",[43,44,48],"a",{"href":45,"rel":46},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhexschool\u002Fweb-layout-training-gulp",[47],"nofollow","web-layout-training-gulp","\" — as the demo, on the ",[28,51,52],{},"feature\u002Fbs5"," branch. This project was created under Node.js 11.7.0.",[17,55,56],{},"You usually don't jump straight from an old Node.js to the latest — you take it in steps. For this project, Node.js 14 is a reasonable target, so:",[58,59,64],"pre",{"className":60,"code":61,"language":62,"meta":63,"style":63},"language-bash shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","nvm use 14 # switch to Node.js 14\nnpm install\n","bash","",[28,65,66,87],{"__ignoreMap":63},[67,68,71,75,79,83],"span",{"class":69,"line":70},"line",1,[67,72,74],{"class":73},"s_sBn","nvm",[67,76,78],{"class":77},"sTRMh"," use",[67,80,82],{"class":81},"sCcAr"," 14",[67,84,86],{"class":85},"sQrFR"," # switch to Node.js 14\n",[67,88,90,93],{"class":69,"line":89},2,[67,91,92],{"class":73},"npm",[67,94,95],{"class":77}," install\n",[17,97,98,99,102],{},"After that, running ",[28,100,101],{},"gulp"," should work fine.",[17,104,105],{},"With the project running on Node.js 14, we're ready to update packages. First, try:",[58,107,109],{"className":60,"code":108,"language":62,"meta":63,"style":63},"npm update --save\n",[28,110,111],{"__ignoreMap":63},[67,112,113,115,118],{"class":69,"line":70},[67,114,92],{"class":73},[67,116,117],{"class":77}," update",[67,119,120],{"class":81}," --save\n",[33,122,123],{},[17,124,125,127,128,131,132,135,136,138],{},[38,126,40],{},"\nJust running ",[28,129,130],{},"npm update"," without ",[28,133,134],{},"--save"," won't actually update versions in package.json. Don't forget ",[28,137,134],{},".",[17,140,141],{},"Now versions in package.json are updated.",[17,143,144],{},[145,146],"img",{"alt":147,"src":148},"Package update","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FNodejs\u002F%E6%9B%B4%E6%96%B0%20npm\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202024-03-21%2011.13.35.png",[12,150,151],{"id":151},"npm-check-updates",[17,153,154,155,158,159,161],{},"You might be wondering — if ",[28,156,157],{},"npm update --save"," already updates packages, why bother with ",[28,160,151],{},"?",[17,163,164,165,167],{},"If you look carefully at your packages, you'll notice many didn't actually update. How do we know? That's where ",[28,166,151],{}," comes in — it checks whether your packages have new versions and updates the versions in package.json.",[17,169,170,171,173],{},"First, install ",[28,172,151],{},". Two options:",[58,175,177],{"className":60,"code":176,"language":62,"meta":63,"style":63},"npm install -g npm-check-updates # global install\n# or\nnpx npm-check-updates # use via npx\n",[28,178,179,195,200],{"__ignoreMap":63},[67,180,181,183,186,189,192],{"class":69,"line":70},[67,182,92],{"class":73},[67,184,185],{"class":77}," install",[67,187,188],{"class":81}," -g",[67,190,191],{"class":77}," npm-check-updates",[67,193,194],{"class":85}," # global install\n",[67,196,197],{"class":69,"line":89},[67,198,199],{"class":85},"# or\n",[67,201,203,206,208],{"class":69,"line":202},3,[67,204,205],{"class":73},"npx",[67,207,191],{"class":77},[67,209,210],{"class":85}," # use via npx\n",[33,212,213],{},[17,214,215,217,219,220,222],{},[38,216,40],{},[28,218,205],{}," lets you use ",[28,221,151],{}," without installing it globally.",[17,224,225,226,228],{},"I'll demo with ",[28,227,205],{}," directly:",[58,230,232],{"className":60,"code":231,"language":62,"meta":63,"style":63},"npx npm-check-updates\n",[28,233,234],{"__ignoreMap":63},[67,235,236,238],{"class":69,"line":70},[67,237,205],{"class":73},[67,239,240],{"class":77}," npm-check-updates\n",[17,242,243],{},"After running this, you'll see a whole bunch of packages that weren't updated...",[17,245,246],{},[145,247],{"alt":248,"src":249},"Update list","https